interpolationMethod.description:
interpolationMethod
The interpolation method if the coordinateScale is greater than 1. This blends the image into noise. For nearest neighbor, use NONE.

InterpolationMethod
An interpolation method (or function) is simply a method of smoothing a position based on surrounding points on a grid. Bicubic for example is smoother, but has 4 times the checks than Bilinear for example. Try using BILINEAR_STARCAST_9 for beautiful results.
    
* Default Value is BILINEAR_STARCAST_6
Must be a valid InterpolationMethod (use ctrl+space for auto complete!)

smartBore.description:
smartBore
If set to true, Iris will try to fill the insides of 'rooms' and 'pockets' where air should fit based off of raytrace checks. This prevents a village house placing in an area where a tree already exists, and instead replaces the parts of the tree where the interior of the structure is. 

This operation does not affect warmed-up generation speed however it does slow down loading objects.

Boolean
* Default Value is false

interval.description:
interval
Iris spins the axis but not freely. For example an interval of 90 would mean 4 possible angles (right angles) degrees. 
Setting this to 0 means totally free rotation.

Note that a lot of structures can have issues with non 90 degree intervals because the minecraft block resolution is so low.

Number
* Default Value is 0.0
* Minimum allowed is 0.0
* Maximum allowed is 360.0
